  "prompt": "What is the weather in Orlando like on June, and how does it differ from the weather in August?",
  "response": "In Orlando, June and August are both part of the summer season and share similar characteristics:\n\nJune:\n- Average high temperatures around 88-92\u00b0F (31-33\u00b0C)\n- Average low temperatures around 72-75\u00b0F (22-24\u00b0C)\n- High humidity levels\n- Frequent afternoon thunderstorms\n- Increased chance of rain compared to drier months\n- Beginning of the hurricane season\n\nAugust:\n- Average high temperatures around 91-93\u00b0F (33-34\u00b0C)\n- Average low temperatures around 74-76\u00b0F (23-24\u00b0C)\n- Very high humidity\n- More frequent and intense afternoon thunderstorms\n- Peak of hurricane season\n- Slightly warmer and more humid than June\n\nThe key differences are:\n- August is slightly warmer\n- August has more intense and frequent thunderstorms\n- August is in the peak of hurricane season\n- August typically has higher humidity levels\n\nBoth months are hot, humid, and characterized by afternoon thunderstorms typical of Florida's summer climate.",
